                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d451">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">832.00 Revolutions/100: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Bahia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Briggs</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bahia</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-10-18T14:00:00-03:00"
                            >October 18, 1930—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 2:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Apparently revolutionists have invaded State of Bahia from Sergipe and Government
                    troops are tearing up the track above Alagoinhas. According to street rumors
                    revolutionists will arrive in two or three days but this is impossible.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Briggs</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
